g:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Horizons:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural projections remain mapped to the 8,447 to 8,477 year-end Wall Street High Call zone on S\u0026amp;P 500 futures.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e Monitor 1.5k MotiveWave volume charts through the 10:00 ET housing release, 10:30 ET crude inventory window, and 13:00 ET 5-Year auction. VAL flushes are buy candidates only when absorption confirms.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Post-Base Phase:\u003c/strong\u003e The June 16-17 cycle base remains the working foundation. Build exposure at high-volume nodes and avoid chasing thin vertical expansions into event risk.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
